def visualization_data(data):
  rtl = lambda w: get_display(reshape(f'{w}'))
  class_text= " ".join(data.tolist())
  COUNTS = Counter(class_text.split())
  counts = {rtl(k):v for k, v in COUNTS.most_common(100)}
  font_file = 'NotoNaskhArabic-Regular.ttf'
  wordcloud = WordCloud(font_path=font_file, width=800, height=500, random_state=21, max_font_size=110).generate_from_frequencies(counts)
  plt.figure(figsize=(10, 7))
  plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation="bilinear")
  plt.axis("off")
  plt.title('The most freq words in tweets:')
  plt.show()

def find_ngrams(data):
  class_text = " ".join(data.tolist())
  tokens= tokenizer.tokenize(class_text)
  #unigram
  print('uni_gram -> HighFreq:')
  unigram_freq = nltk.ngrams(tokens, 1)
  unigram_freq=nltk.FreqDist(unigram_freq)
  print(unigram_freq.most_common()[:10])
  print('uni_gram -> LowFreq:')
  print(unigram_freq.most_common()[-10:])
  print('\n')

  #bigram
  print('bi_gram -> HighFreq:')
  bigram_freq = nltk.ngrams(tokens, 2)
  bigram_freq=nltk.FreqDist(bigram_freq)
  print(bigram_freq.most_common()[:10])
  print('bi_gram -> LowFreq:')
  print(bigram_freq.most_common()[-10:])
  print('\n')

  #trigram
  print('tri_gram -> HighFreq:')
  trigram_freq = nltk.ngrams(tokens, 3)
  trigram_freq=nltk.FreqDist(trigram_freq)
  print(trigram_freq.most_common()[:10])
  print('tri_gram -> LowFreq:')
  print(trigram_freq.most_common()[-10:])

In [ ]:
hashtags = []
def hashtag_extract(data):
    for i in data:
        ht = re.findall(r"#(\w+)", i)
        hashtags.append(ht)
    return hashtags
In [ ]:
def hashtag_visualize(data):
  dff_all = hashtag_extract(data)
  dff_all = sum(dff_all,[])
  dff_all = nltk.FreqDist(dff_all)
  dff_all = pd.DataFrame({'Count': list(dff_all.values()),'Hashtag': list(dff_all.keys())}).sort_values(by='Count', ascending=False)
  print(dff_all.head())
  dff_all[:10].plot(x ='Hashtag', y='Count', kind='bar')

def remove_mintions(tweet,work):
  '''
    
  '''
  if work ==1:
    cleaned_tweet = re.sub(r"@\S+",'',tweet)
  else:
    cleaned_tweet = tweet
  return cleaned_tweet

def remove_urls(tweet,work):
  '''
   
  '''
  if work ==1:
      cleaned_tweet = re.sub(r"(https|http|ftp)?://\S*.((\S*\S*)|(\S*))",'', tweet)
  else:
    cleaned_tweet = tweet
  return cleaned_tweet

def remove_images(tweet,work):
  '''
   
  '''
  if work ==1:
    cleaned_tweet = re.sub(r"pic\.twitter\.com/\S+",'', tweet)
    cleaned_tweet = re.sub("\w+(\.png|\.jpg|\.gif|\.jpeg)", " ", cleaned_tweet)
  else:
    cleaned_tweet = tweet
  return cleaned_tweet

def  remove_duplicated_char(tweet,work):
  '''
      
  '''
  if work ==1:
    cleaned_tweet= re.sub(r'(\w)\1+', r'\1', tweet)
    cleaned_tweet =re.sub(r'(.)\1+', r'\1',cleaned_tweet)
    
  else:
    cleaned_tweet = tweet
  return cleaned_tweet

def  preprocess_tweet(tweet):
    '''
         
    '''
    cleaned_tweet= remove_urls(tweet,1)
    cleaned_tweet= remove_images(cleaned_tweet,1)
    cleaned_tweet= remove_mintions(cleaned_tweet,1)
    cleaned_tweet= remove_duplicated_char(cleaned_tweet,1)
    return cleaned_tweet

def preprocesse(df, text_field):
    df['cleaned_tweet'] = df[text_field].apply(lambda x: preprocess_tweet(str(x)))
    return df

def remove_tweet_digits(tweet,work):
    '''
      
    '''
    if work ==1:
        cleaned_tweet = re.sub(r'[d]+', r'', tweet)
        cleaned_tweet = re.sub(r'([0-9]*\-[0-9]*)*', '', cleaned_tweet)
    else:
        cleaned_tweet = tweet
    return cleaned_tweet

all_stop_words = set(stopwords.words('arabic'))
In [ ]:
def remove_stopword(tweet,work): 
   """Process tweet function.
    Input:
        tweet: a string containing a tweet without removing Arabic stopword
    Output:
        cleaned_tweet: tweet with removing Arabic stopword
    """     
   words= " "
   for t in tweet:
     if t not in all_stop_words:
       words += t + " "

   if work ==1:
    cleaned_tweet = words
   else:
    cleaned_tweet = tweet
   return cleaned_tweet

def remove_all_stopwords(df,text_field):
    df['cleaned_tweet'] = df[text_field].apply(lambda x: " ".join([w for w in str(x).split() if not w in all_stop_words]))
    return df

def remove_tweet_emojies(tweet,work):
    
    """Process tweet function.
    Input:
        tweet: a string containing a tweet without removing Emojies
    Output:
        cleaned_tweet: tweet with removing Emojies
    """     
    emoji_pattern = re.compile("["
        u"\U0001F600-\U0001F64F"  # emoticons
        u"\U0001F300-\U0001F5FF"  # symbols & pictographs
        u"\U0001F680-\U0001F6FF"  # transport & map symbols
        u"\U0001F1E0-\U0001F1FF"  # flags (iOS)
        u"\U0001F1F2-\U0001F1F4"  # Macau flag
        u"\U0001F1E6-\U0001F1FF"  # flags
        u"\U0001F600-\U0001F64F"
        u"\U00002702-\U000027B0"
        u"\U000024C2-\U0001F251"
        u"\U0001f926-\U0001f937"
        u"\U0001F1F2"
        u"\U0001F1F4"
        u"\U0001F620"
        u"\u200d"
        u"\u2640-\u2642"
        "]+", flags=re.UNICODE)
    if work ==1:
       cleaned_tweet = emoji_pattern.sub(r'',tweet)
    else:
      cleaned_tweet = tweet
     
    
    return cleaned_tweet

def remove_punctuation(tweet,work):
   """Process tweet function.
    Input:
        tweet: a string containing a tweet without removing punctuations
    Output:
        cleaned_tweet: tweet after removing punctuations

    """
   if work ==1:
      cleaned_tweet =re.sub('[%s]' % re.escape("""!"#$%&'()*+,-./:;<=>?@[\]^_`{|}~|\|\)|\("""), ' ', tweet)
   else:
     cleaned_tweet = tweet
   return cleaned_tweet

#remove not arabic word from tweet 
def remove_NotArabic_chars(tweet,work):
    """
    Process tweet function.
    Input:
        tweet: a string containing a tweet without changing
    Output:
        cleaned_tweet:A tweet after  remove_NotArabic_chars
    """ 
    if work ==1:
      cleaned_tweet = re.sub(r'[/(){}\[\]\|]', '', tweet)
      cleaned_tweet = re.sub(r'[!$%^?&*><]', '', cleaned_tweet )
      cleaned_tweet = re.sub(r'[\'\".,;+-=]', '', cleaned_tweet )
      cleaned_tweet = re.sub(r'[\n]', '', cleaned_tweet ) # removing \n
      cleaned_tweet = re.sub(r'\s*[A-Za-z]+\b', '' ,cleaned_tweet )# removing English letters
      cleaned_tweet =re.sub(r"\s+",' ',cleaned_tweet) # remove_extra_white_space
    else:
     cleaned_tweet = tweet
    return cleaned_tweet

In [ ]:
def tashaphyne_stemming(tweet,work):
  if work == 1:
    tweet_tokens = tokenizer.tokenize(tweet)
    arepr = pyarabic.arabrepr.ArabicRepr()
    repr = arepr.repr
    ArListem = ArabicLightStemmer()
    output = ""

    for word in tweet_tokens:
        if (word.find("#") == -1): # we dont stemm a hashtag
            stem = ArListem.light_stem(word)
            stem = ArListem.get_stem()
            print(word + " -> "+ stem)
        else:
            stem = word
        output+=(stem + " ")

    cleaned_tweet= "".join(output)
  else:
    cleaned_tweet = tweet
  return cleaned_tweet

import qalsadi.lemmatizer
def qalsadi_lemmatizer(tweet,work):
  lemmer = qalsadi.lemmatizer.Lemmatizer()
  tweet_tokens = tokenizer.tokenize(tweet)
  if work == 1:
    output = ""
    for word in tweet_tokens:
      if (word.find("#") == -1):  # we dont lemmatize a hashtag
        lemma = lemmer.lemmatize(word)
        print(word + " -> "+ lemma)
      else:
        lemma = word
      output+=(lemma + " ")
    cleaned_tweet= "".join(output)
  else:
    cleaned_tweet = tweet
  return cleaned_tweet

#  The converted letters are :
#  The converted lettersinto HAMZA are: WAW_HAMZA,YEH_HAMZA
#  The converted lettersinto ALEF are: ALEF_MADDA,
#  ALEF_HAMZA_ABOVE, ALEF_HAMZA_BELOW ,HAMZA_ABOVE, HAMZA_BELOW
def hamza_normalizing(tweet,work):
  if work ==1:
    cleaned_tweet = arabconst.ALEFAT_PAT.sub(arabconst.ALEF, tweet)
    return arabconst.HAMZAT_PAT.sub(arabconst.HAMZA,cleaned_tweet )
  else:
    return tweet

def spellerrors_normalizing(tweet,work):
  if work ==1:
    cleaned_tweet = re.sub(u'[%s]' % arabconst.TEH_MARBUTA, arabconst.HEH, tweet)
    return re.sub(u'[%s]' % arabconst.ALEF_MAKSURA, arabconst.YEH, cleaned_tweet)
  else:
    return tweet

def preprocessing_final(tweet, flags=[0,1]):
    """Process tweet function.
    Input:
        tweet: a string containing a tweet
        flags: list of "work" values for all functions will called here.
    Output:
        cleaned_tweet: tweet after apply all cleaning and normlizaing functions

    """
    tweet = tweet.lower()
    tweet = re.sub('RT|cc', ' ', tweet)  # remove RT and cc
    tweet = remove_urls(tweet, flags[1])
    tweet = remove_mintions(tweet, flags[1])
    tweet = remove_images(tweet, flags[1])
    tweet = remove_duplicated_char(tweet, flags[1])
    tweet = remove_tweet_emojies(tweet, flags[1])
    tweet = remove_punctuation(tweet, flags[1])
    tweet = remove_tweet_digits(tweet, flags[1])
    tweet = remove_stopword(tweet, flags[1])
    tweet = remove_NotArabic_chars(tweet, flags[1])
    tweet = tashaphyne_stemming(tweet, flags[1])
    tweet = qalsadi_lemmatizer(tweet, flags[1])
    tweet = normalizeArabic(tweet, flags[1])
    tweet = hamza_normalizing(tweet,1)
    tweet = spellerrors_normalizing(tweet,1)
    tweet = strip_tashkeel(tweet,1)
    tweet = strip_tatweel(tweet,1) 
    
    return tweet
